        "text": "Festive\" (Gesen.) \"the dancer\" (Stanley)] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "exalted himself, saying",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [to him self and his confederates], ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "I will be king",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". [It is not difficult to trace this resolve to its sources. They were ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "note_emph",
        "text": "(1)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " his seniority (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 2:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). It is true there was no \"right of primogeniture\" in the Hebrew monarchy. \"The God King had reserved to Himself the choice of the earthly king\" (Keil). David himself was not the eldest, but the youngest brother. At the same time primogeniture, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "ceteris paribus",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", would have, and as a matter of fact had, considerable weight. The firstborn had the birthright; can we doubt he would expect the crown, and think it hard if he were passed over? (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 21:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "note_emph",
        "text": "(2)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " His personal attractions. Adonijah would think that his beauty and stature (Josephus mentions the latter) marked him out, as similar gifts had done Saul (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 9:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "),. for the throne. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "note_emph",
        "text": "(3)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " He was encouraged in his pretensions, if indeed they were not suggested to him, by others, by Joab, for example (see on ver. 7). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "note_emph",
        "text": "(4)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Possibly  love for the beautiful Shunammite and the desire to gain possession of her may have strengthened his resolves. It is noteworthy that he and his beauty are mentioned just after her and hers]: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "and he prepared",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [Hebrews ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "made",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "him chariots and horsemen",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cmt_word",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "him chariots and horsemen",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [rather ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "horses",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
